txt.en:
'You have done much to aid us, [placeholder]... so much so that I wish for you to travel to Dol Amroth. The people there would be well-served to have a skilful [placeholder] at their side.

'The city is a wonder all its own, and if you have never visited it... prepare yourself. It is my opinion that you would be hard-pressed to find a place of greater beauty in Gondor, save perhaps Minas Tirith. I have said enough of the city... it is time you saw it for yourself!

'Go, and seek a guard near the eastern gate - I can hardly keep up with all of the postings lately, so simply tell them I sent you.'

'Ah, so Gilanor sent you? Good man, that one.\n\n'Allow me to welcome you to Dol Amroth, the city of the Prince! You will have ample time to explore, I assure you, so for now, let us speak of other things.'
Heartened by your victories in Edhellond, Gilanor seeks your aid in protecting the great city of Dol Amroth.
The city of Dol Amroth can be found to the west of Ost Lontir.\n\nGilanor has asked you to offer your services to the people of Dol Amroth.
Talk to a guard outside the eastern gate of Dol Amroth
